'''''Bronze Dragon: Conquest of Infinity''''' is a [[role-playing video game]] for the [[Apple II]] published by Commonwealth Software in 1985.

==Gameplay==
''Bronze Dragon: Conquest of Infinity'' is a game in which the fantasy adventuring campaign has a detailed background with 13 plots that the player can choose from.<ref name="CGW32"/>

==Reception==
Johnny Wilson reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "For all of its similarity to other systems, BD is an imaginative game with its own character. The variety of attack options, artifacts, monster attacks, and plot twists makes it a distinctive, enjoyable and satisfying game."<ref name="CGW32">{{cite magazine |last=Wilson |first=Johnny |title=Sports Scoreboard |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=November 1986 |volume=1 |issue=32 |pages=49, 55}}</ref>

